        <h6>August 25</h6>
        <q>The intersection of the roads paralleling the main runway on the west with the lake and beach roads going north and then south to access the north beach runway and parking area. The water is too deep to travel through and loose gravel pile up hampered us also. It flooded up along the stop sign, usually on the beach. No road at all usable, blocked by water, banks and brush.  This completely prevents the use of this travel area in several directions because of high deep water and new loose gravel preventing good traction. We have to travel by boats only, subject to wind conditions over water, or go up over the hills in the woods over longer, slower route, which is also often not usable.</q>
